    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups flattened rice (poha)</li>
            <li>1 large potato, peeled and diced</li>
            <li>1 onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1/2 cup green peas</li>
            <li>1/4 cup peanuts</li>
            <li>1 green chili, chopped</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon mustard seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>8-10 curry leaves</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons oil</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro, chopped (for garnish)</li>
            <li>Lemon wedges (for serving)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2> Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>breakfast</li>
            <li>indian</li>
            <li>veg</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Rinse the flattened rice (poha) under cold water and set aside to drain excess water.</li>
            <li>Heat oil in a pan. Add mustard seeds and let them splutter.</li>
            <li>Add chopped onions, green chili, and curry leaves. Saute until the onions are translucent.</li>
            <li>Add diced potatoes, green peas, and peanuts. Cook until the potatoes are tender.</li>
            <li>Add turmeric powder and salt. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Now, add the rinsed flattened rice (poha) to the pan. Mix gently to combine all the ingredients.</li>
            <li>Cover and let it cook on low heat for 3-5 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve hot with lemon wedges.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Poha!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

